<headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued August 07 at 6:17PM MST until August 07 at 6:45PM MST by NWS Flagstaff</headline>
<description>The National Weather Service in Flagstaff has issued a
* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Yavapai County in west central Arizona...
* Until 645 PM MST.
* At 616 PM MST, a severe thunderstorm was located near Castle Hot
Springs, or 12 miles northwest of New River, moving south at 10
mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Hail damage to vehicles is expected. Expect wind damage
to roofs, siding, and trees.
* Locations impacted include...
Castle Hot Springs and Lake Pleasant.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...1.00 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
